bcl:subparagraph.bcl:text:
the relative importance and sensitivity of different riparian classes of
              streams, wetlands and lakes in conserving water quality, fish habitat, wildlife
              habitat and biodiversity;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
the impact on government granted timber harvesting rights of conserving or
            protecting a cultural heritage resource that is the focus of a traditional use by an
            aboriginal people;

the long term forest health risks that are relevant to species selection for
              the purposes of establishing a free growing stand under section 29 [free
                growing stands] of the Act;

bcl:subparagraph.bcl:text:
the numbers and the distribution of healthy trees of a species referred to
                in subparagraph (i) that are required to adequately stock a free growing stand
                established on the area;
